def: To allure; to tole. [Obs.]With empty hands men may no hawkes tull. Chaucer.

A bridge of which either the whole or a part is made to beraised up, let down, or drawn or turned aside, to admit or hindercommunication at pleasure, as before the gate of a town or castle, orover a navigable river or canal.
Like a lath; long and slender.A lathy horse, all legs and length. R. Browning.
That which (as a drug, or some kinds of food) excites tovenery.
A portion of the southern equatorial current flowing westwardfrom the Fiji Islands to New Guinea.
